Rose also had another go himself and almost went one better than 2012 when his putt hit the pin but failed to fall.

Last up was McIlroy, whose birdie putt from 10-feet on the last hole two years ago helped give him victory in the Dubai showpiece.

The 25-year-old proved it was no fluke by holing an identical putt before Rose stepped up to produce the same result.

But Stenson saved the best until last, gripping his club with just one hand and hooking his left leg around it before putting out in style.

